    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f346a244-090e-4c00-ab78-ba7e3d24fd58",
    "sentence": "Unusually strong payroll job growth in January was followed by little growth at all in February.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c851d3fd-069c-459c-8df6-e0c55ac0fa8f",
    "sentence": "A lot of people are having a very tough time.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1ae81a94-42b1-48e3-a670-45e3135d4303",
    "sentence": "We, we will make that determination meeting by meeting, based on the totality of incoming data and their implications for the outlook for economic activity and inflation.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230503.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230503",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3a8c218d-158d-483b-a0e9-1d1692f68448",
    "sentence": "We will use our tools both to support the economy and a strong labor market and to prevent higher inflation from becoming entrenched.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20211215.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20211215",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "57c95fd5-387e-4638-ad6c-e069d95c1339",
    "sentence": "Do you think it will be several months away?",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2c4ffc22-5b5b-44ba-ad90-3b5291240734",
    "sentence": "Our obligation is to make sure that a one-time increase in the price level does not become an ongoing inflation problem.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20251210.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20251210",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "78a634b1-09db-40d6-a004-0e07fa1fcc1f",
    "sentence": "As indicated in today’s policy statement, the Committee sees the economic recovery as proceeding at a moderate pace.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "16fecf20-0445-49f9-bb66-be87e946c0c9",
    "sentence": "But, based on its current outlook, the Committee judges that it can be patient in doing so.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20141217.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20141217",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "21569c34-d5d4-46b4-8ba2-3f2792f1d3d2",
    "sentence": "Since then, we have seen meaningful cumulative progress in the labor market. For example, since we began the current purchase program, the economy has added about 2.9 million jobs and the unemployment rate has fallen by more than a percentage point, to 7 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20131218.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20131218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e175c342-ce24-42a8-8360-ddab23c411af",
    "sentence": "By getting unemployment down, we hope to bring back to work some of the people who’ve been out of work as long as they have and, in that respect, try to avoid the longer-term consequences of people being out of work for months at a time.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "00c62334-c91d-43b6-b9ce-1fcbca6a2d48",
    "sentence": "In the current environment of sluggish global growth, low inflation, and already very accommodative monetary policy in many advanced economies, investor perceptions of, and appetite for, risk can change abruptly.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160615.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e5446238-acbe-49f0-9241-0f1922324db5",
    "sentence": "Recent indicators point to modest growth of spending and production this quarter.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230201.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230201",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f9d37382-3a31-4c3d-a16b-46d5edfbf201",
    "sentence": "The central tendency of the projections for real GDP growth is 2.0 to 2.2 percent for 2014, down slightly from the June projections.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140917.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140917",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "838332c8-fa5c-4961-9a5c-fdfe663d8c95",
    "sentence": "Compared with the projections made in June, real GDP growth is a touch stronger this year, and inflation—particularly core inflation—is slightly softer this year and next.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170920.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "11d930c5-cdee-4617-aaf2-d87da9c9cd63",
    "sentence": "Household spending is rising at an especially rapid pace, boosted by the ongoing reopening of the economy and ongoing policy support.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210728.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210728",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "11f3d35f-f3ab-4104-ad26-f932bc298402",
    "sentence": "I think this was an important move for us to make.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20211215.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20211215",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5089bd0b-e4c1-4135-b271-dd0531d9c757",
    "sentence": "In providing extraordinary monetary policy accommodation in the aftermath of the crisis, the Committee has not only reduced its target for the federal funds rate to a very low level, but has also expanded the Federal Reserve’s balance sheet substantially.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e347a12b-79b2-4425-a6db-c1106a329de1",
    "sentence": "Over the course of our three previous meetings, we lowered our policy rate by a full percentage point from its peak.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250129.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250129",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b65c94b3-b43f-4fa0-836e-50d31e980213",
    "sentence": "Obviously, it’s not.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "277a3df3-5a9d-4c6d-95e2-dc11026636ee",
    "sentence": "I don’t know—I don’t know what the right way for us to react will be.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250618.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a66c0e14-57b1-4d94-895f-94326d17b43b",
    "sentence": "Inflation has eased significantly over the past two years.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20241107.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20241107",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0c0058cb-7cfd-4194-8b74-a73ba62ac51e",
    "sentence": "If the economy remains solid and inflation persists, we’re prepared to maintain the current target range for the federal funds rate as long as appropriate.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240612.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240612",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "02053383-d175-4a61-a122-269f90043287",
    "sentence": "Yes, so we look at housing—of course, housing is significantly affected by these higher rates, which are really back where they were before the Global Financial Crisis—they’re not historically high, but they’re much higher than they’ve been.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20221102.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "21b535cd-310d-4885-a751-dba025234e55",
    "sentence": "The Committee’s mandate from the Congress is to seek maximum employment and price stability.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20111102.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20111102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "434467cf-3d72-4bee-a4fb-12d729e6f44b",
    "sentence": "It is intended to insure against downside risks from weak global growth and trade policy uncertainty, to help offset the effects these factors are currently having on the economy, and to promote a faster return of inflation to our symmetric 2 percent objective. All of these objectives will support achievement of our overarching goal: to sustain the expansion, with a strong job market and inflation close to our objective, for the benefit of the American people.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190731.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b37f12b5-55dc-44d5-9bbd-83b89f0a3eba",
    "sentence": "This outlook is reflected in the individual economic projections submitted in conjunction with this meeting by the FOMC participants.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20141217.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20141217",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ba2aabca-50c6-4d1a-9999-79bc31f0a6b0",
    "sentence": "For quite some time, inflation has been running below the Committee’s 2 percent longer-run objective. However, we believe this year’s shortfall in inflation primarily reflects developments that are largely unrelated to broader economic conditions. For example, one-off reductions earlier this year in certain categories of prices, such as wireless telephone services, are currently holding down inflation, but these effects should be transitory. Such developments are not uncommon and, as long as inflation expectations remain reasonably well anchored, are not of great concern from a policy perspective because their effects fade away.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170920.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "23ea54c9-323b-43b6-998e-7276d809965a",
    "sentence": "The median inflation projection falls to 2.4 percent in 2026 and 2.1 percent in 2027.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250618.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f9b14dbd-479c-4db6-b894-6363a7b02d82",
    "sentence": "And under normal circumstances, construction, both residential and nonresidential, would be a big part of the recovery process.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b10417cb-8720-4f97-9db7-6c4a93171d9e",
    "sentence": "In conjunction with today’s meeting, FOMC participants—the 7 Board members and 12 Reserve Bank presidents—submitted their individual economic projections and policy assessments for the years 2012 through 2015 and over the longer run.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20120913.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20120913",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fdc051f8-35d0-450c-a764-693580d115f1",
    "sentence": "The Committee recognizes that inflation persistently below its objective could pose risks to economic performance, and we will continue to monitor inflation developments closely. However, the unwinding of some transitory factors has led to moderately higher inflation recently, as expected.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c9cae05f-507e-4fb0-87ac-07efd143d83d",
    "sentence": "We’re talking about—when you’re projecting the economy, you know, three years out, two years out, you’re talking about high uncertainty.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20241218.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20241218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "37330213-5d98-43e0-bfd6-65cc9c29a1c2",
    "sentence": "I can’t tell you what the longer-run normal level of reserve balances will be because that will depend on the Committee’s eventual decisions about how to implement monetary policy most efficiently and effectively in the longer run, as well as a number of as-yet unknown elements, including the banking system’s future demand for reserves and various factors that may affect the daily supply of reserves.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170614.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170614",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c6ac0c3d-22f6-4cd4-b8a8-adf1f7cce900",
    "sentence": "That expectation is based on our view that this rate remains somewhat below its neutral level—that is, the level that is neither expansionary nor contractionary and keeps the economy operating on an even keel.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20171213.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20171213",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
